---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import PricingTable from '../components/PricingTable.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Pricing — Rajan Shrestha"
  description="Automation builds and retainers for GTM, RevOps, and supply chain teams. One-time builds from $1,500, retainers from $500/mo."
>
  <div class="container pricing-page">
    <header class="pricing-header section" data-reveal>
      <span class="label">Pricing</span>
      <h1 class="pricing-title">
        Pay for a build,<br>
        <em>not a headcount</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="pricing-intro">
        Every engagement starts as a fixed-price build — you know the cost before
        we start. Most clients add a monthly retainer afterward to keep the
        system maintained and growing as their process changes.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="section" aria-label="Pricing tiers">
      <PricingTable />
    </section>

    <section class="section pricing-faq">
      <h2 data-reveal>How this works</h2>
      <div class="faq-item" data-reveal>
        <h3>Why a build fee plus a retainer?</h3>
        <p>
          The build fee covers the initial system — discovery, design, and
          implementation. The retainer covers what comes after: monitoring,
          fixing what breaks when an upstream API changes, and adding new
          workflows as your process evolves. You're never required to take
          the retainer, but most clients do once the system is live and
          they see what it's worth maintaining.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item" data-reveal>
        <h3>What determines where I land in a price range?</h3>
        <p>
          Number of integrations, whether the logic needs custom Python
          (versus standard n8n nodes), and how much historical data needs
          migrating or cleaning. You'll get an exact number after a short
          scoping call — not a guess.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item" data-reveal>
        <h3>Do you work outside GTM, RevOps, and supply chain?</h3>
        <p>
          Those are where I specialize because the patterns repeat —
          pricing logic, lead routing, ops reporting, route optimization.
          If your problem looks like one of the case studies, it's
          probably a fit.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section pricing-cta-section" data-reveal>
      <h2>Not sure which tier fits?</h2>
      <p>
        Book a 20-minute call — I'll scope the build and give you an exact
        number, not a range.
      </p>
      <button
        type="button"
        class="btn btn-primary pricing-final-cta"
        data-magnetic
        data-cal-link="rajan10x/meeting-ai"
        data-cal-namespace="meeting-ai"
        data-cal-config={`{"layout":"month_view"}`}
      >
        Book a call →
      </button>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .pricing-page {
    padding-bottom: 80px;
  }

  .pricing-header {
    padding-top: 64px;
  }

  .label {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .pricing-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(30px, 5vw, 48px);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--parchment);
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -1px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .pricing-title em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--parchment-2);
  }

  .pricing-intro {
    max-width: 520px;
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  .pricing-faq h2 {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .faq-item {
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .faq-item:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .faq-item h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--parchment-2);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .faq-item p {
    font-size: 13px;
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .pricing-cta-section {
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .pricing-cta-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .pricing-cta-section p {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .pricing-header { padding-top: 44px; }
  }
</style>
